Method Detail

getPersistentThreadInstance

public PersistentThread getPersistentThreadInstance()
Obtains the thread that runs the Guidance routine. On first call to this method, the PersistentThread is created. But since two or more instances of Guidance should not be run concurrently, subsequent calls to this method return only that first thread.

Returns:
The PersistentThread that runs Guidance routine.
